         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div type="translation" source="#jmr-jbwp-rgg2003" xml:lang="en"><p>i. The Pharos.</p>
            <p>ii. This work too came into being in the time of Makarios the most holy bishop in indiction year 3.</p>
            <p>iii. Euphrates.</p>
            <p>iv. Castalia.</p>
            <p>v. Tigris.</p>
            <p>vi. Geon.</p>
            <p>vii. Renewal.</p>
            <p>viii. Phison.</p>
            <p>ix. Adornment.</p>
            <p>x. The new city Theodorias.</p>
            <p>xi. Foundation.</p></div>
            </div>
        
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>For the building, see Christian Monuments, 273-286.</p>
            <!-- <p>This is the constructed of the two churches on the site and maybe the product of a schismatic group.
               For the personifications of Κόσμησις, Κτίσις and Ἀνανέωσις cf. e.g. IGLC III, 750, 771, 1016, 1119 
               from Antioch and the neighbourhood. In Cyrenaica see also at Ras el Hilal. </p>-->

            <!-- ** More commentary in CMC. Anything to copy here, or just cite? ** -->
            <p>The new city, presumably the settlement at Gasr Leibia, is not otherwise attested and
               must have been quite small. It was apparently named for the Empress Theodora, and was
               probably therefore founded during her lifetime. The only year of her reign which was
               the third of an indiction (see ii, line 7) was C.E. 539.</p>
         </div>
         
